23/10/2003
HELSINKI, Finland -- The government adopted and submitted to parliament Wednesday (22 October) a proposal for ratification of the Stabilisation and Association Agreement between Croatia and the EU.
The news came as Croatian President Stipe Mesic paid an official visit to Helsinki, part of his tour of Scandinavian countries.
Meeting Mesic, Finnish President Tarja Halonen said she expected parliament to ratify the SAA within months.
In other news, GONG, a Croatian NGO, says it plans to recruit 3,500 observers to monitor next month's parliamentary elections.
The Croatian National Democratic Institute, the OSCE Mission and the embassies of Canada and Britain will co-finance GONG's election activities, contributing about 200,000 euros.
(MediaScan, HINA, BBC - 22/10/03)
